Ordered from here (online) for my company ( a not for profit organization). As a confirmation, the store employee called to verify the order. I informed the employee that I have a completed tax exemption. He informed me that I could only use the exemption in person although the store has a working fax machine. I told him that's a silly request and he can't possibly expect a business to travel to their store to hand deliver a form that could be faxed. He said those are the orders from the store owners. I asked to speak to a manager and he said he was the manager. Well, store owners you need to do better if you expect reputable businesses to continue doing business with you. Every other restaurant receives tax exemptions via email or fax. This is a poor business practice.
